Here's a recommended structure:

**1. Abstract the HTTP client behind an interface**

```csharp
public interface IApiClient
{
    Task<WeatherData> GetWeatherAsync(string city);
}

public class ApiClient : IApiClient
{
    private readonly HttpClient _http;
    public ApiClient(HttpClient http) => _http = http;

    public async Task<WeatherData> GetWeatherAsync(string city)
    {
        var resp = await _http.GetFromJsonAsync<WeatherData>($"/weather?city={city}");
        return resp!;
    }
}
```

**2. Inject the interface into your tool class**

```csharp
[McpServerToolType]
public class WeatherTools
{
    private readonly IApiClient _api;
    public WeatherTools(IApiClient api) => _api = api;

    [McpServerTool, Description("Get weather for a city")]
    public async Task<string> GetWeather(string city)
    {
        var data = await _api.GetWeatherAsync(city);
        return $"{data.TempF}°F, {data.Condition}";
    }
}
```

**3. Create the test project**

```
MyMcpServer/
├── src/
│   └── MyMcpServer/
│       ├── MyMcpServer.csproj
│       ├── ApiClient.cs
│       └── WeatherTools.cs
└── tests/
    └── MyMcpServer.Tests/
        ├── MyMcpServer.Tests.csproj
        └── WeatherToolsTests.cs
```

```bash
dotnet new xunit -o tests/MyMcpServer.Tests
cd tests/MyMcpServer.Tests
dotnet add reference ../../src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj
dotnet add package NSubstitute   # or Moq
```

**4. Write tests with a mock**

```csharp
using NSubstitute;

public class WeatherToolsTests
{
    [Fact]
    public async Task GetWeather_ReturnsFormattedString()
    {
        // Arrange
        var api = Substitute.For<IApiClient>();
        api.GetWeatherAsync("Seattle")
           .Returns(new WeatherData { TempF = 55, Condition = "Cloudy" });

        var tools = new WeatherTools(api);

        // Act
        var result = await tools.GetWeather("Seattle");

        // Assert
        Assert.Equal("55°F, Cloudy", result);
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task GetWeather_WhenApiFails_ThrowsException()
    {
        var api = Substitute.For<IApiClient>();
        api.GetWeatherAsync(Arg.Any<string>())
           .ThrowsAsync(new HttpRequestException("timeout"));

        var tools = new WeatherTools(api);

        await Assert.ThrowsAsync<HttpRequestException>(
            () => tools.GetWeather("nowhere"));
    }
}
```

**Key principles:**

| Concern | Approach |
|---|---|
| **Decouple** HTTP from tools | Interface (`IApiClient`) + DI |
| **Mock framework** | NSubstitute, Moq, or FakeItEasy |
| **Test framework** | xUnit, NUnit, or MSTest |
| **Test the tool directly** | Call the method, assert the return value |
| **Error paths** | Mock exceptions to verify handling |

This lets you test all your tool logic—formatting, branching, error handling—without any network calls.
